The government of Nigeria has commenced construction of a Potato Tissue Culture Lab in Plateau State following African Development Bank (AfDB)  approving US $3.38m loan set for the project. Speaking at the ground-breaking ceremony, the Plateau State Governor, Simon Lalong said that the tissue culture lab is intended to improve potato yields in the Plateau State by providing clean seed.  Also Read:South Africa to construct rooftop gardens in Johannesburg  The project will be done under the auspices of the Potato Value Chain Support Project of the African Development Bank, which translates that in no distance future, the state government will be exporting to other countries of the world, not only Irish Potatoes but also its allied products from the Potato Value Chain.  